	<!-- TEXT  -->
	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_DESCRIPTION">
			<Text>When Two Tribes Go To War</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_HELP">
			<Text>The tribes living around Uluru have sent a delegate to treat with us, Your Mightiness[NEWLINE]He's in the reception chamber, lecturing the guards on some Lizard Woman.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_HELP_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>The Natural Wonder permenantly yields +1 [ICON_PEACE] Faith, [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism and [ICON_GOLDEN_AGE] Golden Age Points.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_HELP_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>The curse claims {2_InstantYield}. The Shrine in the City gains +3 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_HELP_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>Spend {2_InstantYield} to receive a free Zoo, which yields an additional +2 [ICON_RESEARCH] Science and +2 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_HELP_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>The local Hotel yields +10 [ICON_GOLD] Gold and +10 [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism. However, the Natural Wonder loses up to -10 [ICON_PEACE] Faith.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_1">
			<Text>*The natives have completed their dreamwalk, it is once again respectful for us to go about our business near Uluru*[NEWLINE]We continue to uphold our treaty with those who live around Uluru. Peace go with you.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_2">
			<Text>*An ancient curse has been claiming the lives of those who have taken rocks from Uluru. The shaman warns that they must be returned!*[NEWLINE]How disturbing. We should erect a memorial at the local Shrine, that others do not make this same mistake.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_3">
			<Text>*The natives do not wish our researchers to continue interfering with the local wildlife*[NEWLINE]In this matter, your people must trust me to have both our best interests at heart. Conservation and close study is the only way to protect these unique species.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CITY_EVENT_NW_ULURU_DESCRIPTION_CHOICE_4">
			<Text>*The shaman is incensed that the Governor is allowing hikers to scale Uluru*[NEWLINE]Much time has past since first we spoke as equals. My people have grown mighty, and yours have not. You will accede to this...</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
